article.headline: Jackson St. 57, Grambling St. 46
article.story: GRAMBLING, La. -- Kelsey Howard scored 21 points on 8-of-18 shooting from the field, and Jackson State kept Grambling State winless with a 57-46 victory in a Southwestern Athletic Conference game on Saturday night. Christian Williams had 12 points, and Sydney Coleman contributed nine points and six rebounds for Jackson State (2-14, 1-6), which outscored Grambling State 33-20 in the second half. Jackson State snapped a six-game losing streak -- all in the conference -- with the win. The Tigers' only other victory was 91-82 at Seattle on Dec. 17. Steven Dandridge scored 11 points, Terry Rose had 10 points and six rebounds and Peter Robertson scored 10 for Grambling State (0-16, 0-7). Jackson State won the turnover battle 12-5, leading to a 16-4 advantage in points off turnovers. Jackson State shot 6 of 14 from beyond the arc to Grambling State's 2 of 8.
